00:06:38.030 --> 00:06:44.450
And the other part is a
little more complicated.

00:06:44.450 --> 00:06:48.620
So let's do this.

00:06:48.620 --> 00:06:59.400
And consider the case if
qi is different from qj,

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:03.460
I claim i can prove
this property.

00:07:03.460 --> 00:07:06.250
We can prove this
orthonormality.

00:07:06.250 --> 00:07:17.320
So start with the integral
dx of psi i star q psi j.

00:07:22.070 --> 00:07:27.460
Well, q out here at psi j is qj.

00:07:27.460 --> 00:07:38.230
So this is integral dx
psi i star qj psi j.

00:07:38.230 --> 00:07:44.772
And therefore, it's equal to qj
times integral psi i star psi

00:07:44.772 --> 00:07:46.100
j.

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:53.880
I simplified this by
just enervating it.

00:07:53.880 --> 00:07:58.310
Because psi i and psi
j are eigenstates of q.

00:07:58.310 --> 00:08:01.760
Now, the other thing I
can do is use the property

00:08:01.760 --> 00:08:06.890
that q is Hermitant and move
the q to act on this function.

00:08:06.890 --> 00:08:18.270
So this is equal to integral
dx q i psi i star psi j.

00:08:18.270 --> 00:08:22.390
And now I can keep
simplifying as well.

00:08:22.390 --> 00:08:23.420
And I have dx.

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:33.081
And then I have the complex
